message: DRR - Cpptraj: Add Atom constructor for use with Tinker files. Read box information when opening Tinker file if present. Add routine to read atom information from Tinker file. Add parm reader for Tinker file.
DRR - Cpptraj: Remove obsolete ArgList function. Add Tinker parm file.
DRR - Cpptraj: Slight modification to Tinker recognition routine  titles can be any size apparently and contain whitespace. Also set topology title/filename.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix ordering of enumerated type.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add Tinker trajectory file
DRR - Cpptraj: Move Tinker file detection ahead of Amber Traj since Tinker file with box coords can look like an Amber Traj.
DRR - Cpptraj: Properly update frame count
DRR - Cpptraj: Add routine to determine residue info from molecules if no residue info present.

DRR - Cpptraj: In FileName  record directory prefix. In lifetime analysis use directory prefix + prefix + base filename instead of just prepending the prefix (which results in an error when not writing to the same directory).
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix lifetime curve filename when not in same directory
DRR - Cpptraj: Trap mask errors in some commands.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add check for misplaced operators in atom masks that can lead to segfaults.
DRR - Cpptraj: Trap errors when opening files for writing in modes analysis. Enable eigenvalue fraction analysis in modes.
DRR - Cpptraj: In rotdif  make 'out' an alias for 'outfile'.
DRR - Cpptraj: corrout rotdif option now prints time correlation functions for all vectors.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix lifetime curve file name setup when not using windows
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix AddVal function so that previous values are actually incremented (fixes solvent hbond lifetime calculation bug)
DRR - Cpptraj: Add more feedback for rotdif gridsearch option.
DRR - Cpptraj: Use map when reading in groups from remd.dim in case they are out of order.
DRR - Cpptraj: During remlog read use given group number in MREMD logs.
DRR - Cpptraj: Use internal buffer in BufferedLine::GetLine routine instead of CpptrajFile::GetLine
DRR - Cpptraj: Add missing braces.

DRR - Cpptraj: Fix up nmwiz output  add more error checking  add option to use an atom mask so topology can match eigenvectors  move nmwiz output code into Analysis_Matrix since it is only needed/used there.
DRR - Cpptraj: Allow writing of topologies from COORDS datasets with parmwrite
Fix tinker file autodetect.
Merge branch 'master' of git.ambermd.org:amber
DRR - Cpptraj: Remove debug message.
DRR - Cpptraj: Protect pucker analysis from invalid pucker values than can lead to segfault.
DRR - Cpptraj: Update help.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add 'datafilter' command  allows 'filter' action to be run separate from trajectory processing.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add #s to error message.
DRR - Cpptraj: In pairwise  get reference keywords before data set name  fix bug that prevented delta Es from ever being calculated.

DRR - Cpptraj: Change OpenMP loop variables from unsigned to signed to get rid of errors like "undefined reference to `__kmpc_for_static_init_4u'"  apparently certain OpenMP implementations cannot handle unsigned variables in 'for' blocks.
Merge branch 'master' of git.ambermd.org:amber
DRR - Cpptraj: Change 'modes' output format to make it more amenable for reading into other graphing programs.
DRR - Cpptraj: Make command line mask routines print only mask information - all other output is suppressed to make scripting easier.
DRR - Cpptraj: Replace all instances of SILENT_EXIT with SetWorldSilent(true) and loudPrintf  this way all extraneous output is avoided for command-line flags.
DRR - Cpptraj: Modify DihedralSearch so that all 4 atoms must be connected by bonds  prevents fake 'detection' of dihedrals between separate molecules.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix 2 character element name recognition in PDB files.
DRR - Cpptraj: Make 'AddByMask' error a fatal error for Action_Average.
DRR - CPPTRAJ: Protect torsion analysis from invalid torsion values that can lead to segfault.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add option to write epsilon vs number of clusters.
DRR - Cpptraj: Update version number

DRR - Cpptraj: Topology now include complete replica dim info if present in traj  and can be set with ensemble size. Trajin now returns complete replica dim info. Add ability to write a 4-dim Netcdf ensemble trajectory  but not yet fully implemented. Increment version and internal version #s.
DRR - Cpptraj: Attempt to add indices write  something still seems wrong though  needs more debugging.
DRR - Cpptraj: Trap output trajectory write errors when !exitOnError
DRR - Cpptraj: Add DataIO class for creating vector psuedo trajectories  will replace trajout keyword in vector action
DRR - Cpptraj: For 'writedata' print info on what file format is being used.
DRR - Cpptraj: Use DataIO_VecTraj class for creating vector pseudo trajectory
Merge branch 'cpptraj-dev' into cpptraj-dev-remdEnsembleTrajFmt
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix wrong VID for indices (doesnt matter for release since indices info not present)

DRR - Cpptraj: Switch to using std::vector<int> for remd_indices_ instead of a C-array  which makes lots of code much  much easier to read  cleaner  and safer. I originally didn't use vector since I needed to interface with the NetCDF C routines  but I think I've thoroughly convinced myself that std::vector storage is *always* contiguous. If there is some weird C++ implementation out there where this is not the case it's violating the '03 standard anyway  which at this point (11 years on) should be the minimum we support anyway.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add copy of replica indices where missing
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix typo
Merge branch 'cpptraj-dev' into cpptraj-dev-remdEnsembleTrajFmt

DRR - Cpptraj: Fix bug  when ensemble processing with a single thread it was possible for subsequent ensemble members to work on a modified parm instead of the original one (e.g. for actions like strip/closest)  which could lead to unintended consequences.
Merge branch 'cpptraj-dev' into cpptraj-dev-remdEnsembleTrajFmt
DRR - Cpptraj: Remove debug info from strip and add const for MPI compile
DRR - Cpptraj: Change remd_indices type back to std::vector<int>  using &v[0] to interface with MPI routines now. Send/receive frame replica indices.

DRR - Cpptraj: Split Trajout into Trajout_Single and Trajout_Multi  ensemble trajectory handling will now be done on the level of Trajout instead of CpptrajState. This is to enable later Trajin_Ensemble/Trajout_Ensemble. Default format for TrajectoryFile::GetFormatFromArg is now UNKNOWN instead of AMBERTRAJ.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add InitEnsembleTrajWrite() function back to Trajout_Single  needed for writing single trajectories from ensemble-aware Actions.

DRR - Cpptraj: Make actions/analyses use Trajout_Single. Only a single TrajoutList for ensemble trajout now  ensemble trajout list is created based on existing trajout list. Onlymembers keyword now processed on the level of Trajout instead of TrajoutList. Ensure actual ensemble size is used when setting up ensemble trajout list even when MPI (Trajout_Multi requires actual # to set up onlymembers even though it is not used afterwards) - probably will pass in some additional info later on (temperatures etc). Actions are performed prior to trajectory output  TrajoutList has already-sorted list of frame pointers passed to it (removing need for Frame indices to also be passed in).
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix bug that caused segfault with onlyframes in serial ensemble mode trajout.
DRR - Cpptraj: Remove unneeded include

DRR - Cpptraj: Move towards using Frame pointer array for sorting ensemble frames inside Trajin_Multi so nothing needs to happen in CpptrajState  can probably get rid of frame indices outside of Frame now. Fix ensemble output traj info reporting in MPI  could segfault when onlyframes skipped the lowest replica.

DRR - Cpptraj: Use SortedFrames for actions/trajectory output  i.e. let Trajin_Multi take care of all sorting. Split output trajectory topology-related setup from write  WriteFrame() is now a placeholder function for actions to use  but should maybe eventually be retired.
DRR - Cpptraj: frame index array only needed for MPI so each thread knows where to send/receive frames. Fix NOSORT case.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix TIMER compile
DRR - Cpptraj: Create separate file for definition of FramePtrArray. Initial incarnation of the Trajout_Ensemble class for writing ensemble to single trajectory file.

DRR - Cpptraj: Update references to FramePtrArray. Create functions in TrajectoryIO for single ensemble trajectory file write. Add 'ensemble' keyword to 'trajout' to denote single ensemble trajectory file desired. Update dependencies.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add Traj_NcEnsemble TrajectoryIO class. Make ensemble size < 1 an error for NC_AMBERENSEMBLE
DRR - Cpptraj: Add missing function def
DRR - Cpptraj: Since frame dimension is unlimited it must be the lowest dimension.
DRR - Cpptraj: Finish netcdf ensemble frame write.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add options to write temperature/velocity to nc ensemble  implement write help and add code comments.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix typo
DRR - Cpptraj: Namespace for for holding replica-related stuff.
DRR - Cpptraj: Implement single ensemble file read. A bit clunky right now  will need to streamline later. Maybe make separate trajin lists  or make Trajin objects take a trajectoryIO.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add Trajin_Ensemble class.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix ensemble trajectory read/write  need to reset the atom count after it changes for  remd_indices etc. Remove debug info  add routine to debug netcdf indices.
DRR - Cpptraj: Deal with BadEnsemble correctly

DRR - Cpptraj: Add second array of Trajout* to TrajoutList to hold active output traj sets (sets for which current parm matches init parm). Remove that check from the Trajout level now  and remove TrajIsOpen check from Write routines since they should never be called if not set up.

DRR - Cpptraj: Fix bug where segfault could occur when running secstruct with ptrajformat if line length became > CpptrajFile internal buffer size. Now when ptrajformat each residue gets a string dataset  similar to the default output with integer data set.
DRR - Cpptraj: Add 'assignout' keyword to secstruct: prints overall secondary structure assignment for each residue in a manner similar to the PDB website.

DRR - Cpptraj: Clean up Trajin classes. Make Trajin_Multi timing data specific to Trajin_Multi.

DRR - Cpptraj: Some changes to get Traj_NcEnsemble working in parallel. Each thread will read 1 frame. Disable if parallel netcdf not present  as this is required for writing in parallel (reading in parallel *might* be ok  but not allowed for now).

DRR - Cpptraj: Move Frame parallel send/receive routines to inside Frame itself.

DRR - Cpptraj: Implement single file ensemble trajectory read in parallel. Right now sorting is done the same way as with individual files  but in the future it may be more optimal to do the sorting at the level of TrajectoryIO.
DRR - Cpptraj: In MPI  only need to allocate 2 frames (not the entire ensemble).
DRR - Cpptraj: Do not call ncmpi_sync since it has a huge performance hit (may need to enable or add option to enable later). Remove/reorganize debug info.
DRR - Cpptraj: Correct serial compile issues
DRR - Cpptraj: Masks must have '@'  ':'  or '*'. Do not search for % or / as they are not valid without @ anyway.

DRR - Cpptraj: Consolidate common functionality between Trajin_Multi and Trajin_Ensemble  Trajin_Multi now only uses memory for 2 frames in MPI instead of worldsize frames. Fix MPI+TIMER compile.

DRR - Cpptraj: Fix DSSP calc so it better takes into account SS priority  which fixes odd SS patterns reported by H. Huang from the Simmerling group (e.g. 2-residue alpha helices). DRR - Cpptraj: In DSSP  properly initialize some variables. Clean up comments  add option to print total SS observed per frame for each SS type.
DRR - Cpptraj: Fix the running average calculation. Previously you would just get out what you put in.
DRR - Cpptraj: Remove 'none' from total DSSP output so that the sets line up with those from sum output.

DRR - Cpptraj: Give bounds action the ability to create a grid (with an optional buffer of bins). This means no longer having to guess grid sizes  first pass uses bounds to create grid with given spacing centered appropriately  second pass does the gridding.

Only have specialized routine for getting reference frame via arg list (ref  refindex  reference). Fix data set wildcard matching to account for file name if present. DRR - Cpptraj: Another significant change to data set handling in DataIO classes. For output  DataSet routine now has Coords() routine that returns the value of the coordinate instead of writing it to a file  should be more efficient in cases where the same coordinate has to be written over and over. Should be OK  right now there is no case where the coordinate is anything but a double precision value. Fix up Gnuplot output so that TextFormat and DataSet::SizeArray are used. Appending on data set reading is now done at the time of the read - no more buffering and potentially converting from DataSet_double to DataSet_XYMESH. All numerical data sets are now read in as XYMESH  this will cost more memory but is ultimately much easier to maintain - Grace and Std DataIO input both changed this way. Consolidate RemoveSet/PopSet in DataSetList and get rid of obsolete ParseArgString header. Add TextFormat routine for changing format width only.
